{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Epic expanded from the original token-chunking placeholder into a unified, sequenced plan (design session, Joe). Decisions: (1) PULL the drift-refresh→workflow-engine migration INTO scope and do it FIRST (WS1) so the bespoke pass2_verify/_run_passes/verifier_cfg second verify path is deleted and chunking becomes a single-site change — resolves the prior 'no two divergent batching rules' fork. (2) Reproduce the verifier Sonnet-downgrade declaratively as a per-step model: key (resolve_model/WS-D3, operator override preserved), NOT via bespoke verifier_cfg. (3) Because that makes a per-step model: key first-class on a shipped gate workflow, the visual editor must surface + round-trip-preserve it (WS2) — today only the workflow-level model is carried in BPMN, so editing in the visual editor could silently drop a step's model. (4) The coach-call parity nit (gate coach_notes on surviving>0) is folded in as its own task (WS4). Token estimator reuses est_tokens (chars/4) + largest_window_tokens; oversized single finding escalates the model then falls back to INDETERMINATE rather than silent-drop. Next: review-plan this epic, then decompose WS1-WS4 into child stories/tasks before claiming."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782580850486406001,"uuid":"dd0d10e7-c632-4ae4-972a-e1a185eaa40b"}